  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "The first strategy is called the \"Best-Among-K Strategy\".",
    "For each window 𝑤 in the pool and a set of 𝐾 alternative models 𝐻, the LLM is prompted to determine which explanation of 𝑤 is the best among the ones in 𝐻.",
    "Then, we assign a score with value 1 to the model that provided the best explanation, while the others are scored 0.",
    "When the explanation selected by the LLM is actually generated by more than one model in 𝐻, we assign a score of value 1 to all models that generated that explanation.",
    "At the end of this process, the model in 𝐻 with the highest score is considered the best."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}